When buying a car, you have a range of purchasing decisions to make. Not only do you need to pick the make and model, but you also need to decide if you want to buy a new or used car. There are pros and cons to going either route. So, to help you make the best choice for your needs and your budget, motus.cars, a leading online automotive marketplace that’s supported by Motus Ford (previously Imperial Ford), highlights the advantages and disadvantages of both: Buying a car should always be a practical decision, one you can comfortably afford to live with. Motus.cars offers a helpful affordability calculator to assist you to work  out what you can afford. Once you’ve determined your budget, the digital platform allows you to conveniently shop for both new and pre-owned cars from a nationwide network of 340 Motus dealers at a single online location. Best of all, it gives you the ability to compare cars across all available brands as well as across the new, used and demo categories, so you can be sure to find the option that’ll give you the most value for your money. Motus.cars offers more than 7,000 Motus-certified, pre-owned vehicles for sale. So, if you’ve decided to go the used car route, chances are you will find your dream ride on its website. You can shop with confidence and peace of mind as the company owns all the cars listed. And, if you’ve decided the new car route is your best bet, motus.cars offers the latest promotional deals so you’ll find new vehicles at terrific prices. Visit the motus.cars blog for more valuable tips and join the conversation on Facebook, and Twitter. This article was paid for by motus.cars.